'''Gatekeeping''' is the process of controlling the rate at which students progress to more advanced levels of study in the academic setting.  The term can also be more widely applied to refer to the social structures which test individuals for a certain level of understanding before allowing them to perform certain social functions (e.g. [[medical education]] to become a [[Physician|medical doctor]]).

